&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Darlington Urgent treatment centre is one of five centres across County Durham and Darlington NHS Foundation trust.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;The trust has an integrated Urgent Treatment and Emergency Department service and requires an enthusiastic, forward thinking RGN/paramedic&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span&gt;with additional clinical skills qualification and experience working autonomously in a heath care setting to provide telephone and face to face consultations for patients presenting with unscheduled Primary care conditions, minor illness and minor injuries.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;The post holder we be required to deliver an advanced level of clinical practice within the field of Unscheduled and emergency care. Working within local and nationally agreed protocols and guidelines, the Practitioner will exercises independent judgment to assess, investigate, diagnose, plan, implement and evaluate the clinical care and management of urgent care and emergency patients. They will work alongside and support the education and development of both nursing and medical colleagues.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;A prescribing qualification is desirable.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;For further information please contact Lesley Morgan Urgent Care tem manager via e-mail &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span&gt;lesley.morgan10@nhs.net&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span&gt; of telephone 01325 743472.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
